## Sleep-gate shard (polysomnography → eligibility inputs)

**QPU.Datashard (.aln)**

```aln
aln
aln file xr-sleep.physio-gate.v1.aln
QPU.Datashard Sleep-physiology gate for dream-gaming eligibility

path,entitytype,field,key,value,datatype,constraints,notes
sleep.subject,subject,scalar,subjectId,,string,primarykey,Augmented user ID
sleep.subject,subject,enum,sleepStage,unknown,string,wake,N1,N2,N3,REM,unknown,Polysomnography-derived stage
sleep.subject,subject,scalar,psychRiskScore,0.0,float,range0,1,Continuous psych-risk R
sleep.subject,subject,scalar,enStasisScore,1.0,float,range0,1,Inner stability Es
sleep.subject,subject,scalar,sleepToken,0.0,float,range0,1,Deep-sleep token S from PSG/actigraphy
sleep.subject,subject,flag,hasDaytimeActivityProof,false,bool,nonnull,True when activity budget met

sleep-gate.rule,rule,scalar,ruleId,allow-dream-gaming,string,primarykey,Eligibility gate
sleep-gate.rule,rule,condition,allowGaming,"sleepStage in [N2,N3] AND hasDaytimeActivityProof == true",expression,Only stable deep sleep with activity proof
sleep-gate.rule,rule,condition,denyGaming,"sleepStage in [wake,N1,REM] OR hasDaytimeActivityProof == false",expression,Block outside safe window
```

- Mathematical solution: The shard exposes S (sleepToken), R (psychRiskScore), and Es (enStasisScore) as clamped $[0,1]$ scalars; any engine reading these and applying the same clamps will compute identical inputs to the eligibility function $E = S(1-R)E_s$.[^3_1]
- Scientific grounding: Using PSG/actigraphy for sleep stage plus psych-risk vectors and stability metrics reflects sleep-lab practice where N2/N3 windows with low arousal are treated as safest for stimulation and state transitions.[^3_3]
- Legal terms (≥100 chars): Sleep-physiology inputs SHALL be limited to clinically validated variables (sleep stage, autonomic risk, stability), SHALL be captured under human-subject protections, and SHALL never encode raw dream narratives or beliefs; these parameters MAY gate access to dream-gaming but SHALL not be reused for employment, insurance, or criminal decisions.[^3_3]
- Geographical evidence: Boston, USA (sleep labs), Geneva, Switzerland (WHO neurotech and mental privacy), Santiago, Chile (neurorights pilots covering sleep and mental integrity), Brussels, Belgium (AI Act risk categories including neurotech), Phoenix, Arizona, USA (your lab PSG/XR integration context).[^3_1][^3_3]

