## Nanoswarm / Cyberswarm dose envelope shard

**QPU.Datashard (.aln)**

```aln
aln
aln file xr-nano.cyberswarm-dose-envelope.v1.aln
QPU.Datashard Cyberswarm doseRatio and psychrisk envelope for sleep-gated dream-gaming

path,entitytype,field,key,value,datatype,constraints,notes
nano.sub,substrate,scalar,substrateId,PHX-Cyberswarm-01,string,primarykey,Logical Cyberswarm substrate
nano.sub,substrate,scalar,maxDoseGyPerDay,0.05,float,range0,0.1,Max daily equivalent dose
nano.sub,substrate,scalar,maxSARWkg,0.4,float,range0,1.6,Max SAR ceiling

nano.dose,view,scalar,dailyDoseGy,0.0,float,range0,10,Accumulated daily dose
nano.dose,view,scalar,maxDoseGy,,float,range0,0.1,Imported from nano.sub
nano.dose,view,formula,doseRatio,"dailyDoseGy / maxDoseGy",string,readonly,Dr = Dday/Dmax
nano.dose,view,condition,allowOps,"doseRatio <= 1.0",expression,Allow nanoswarm ops in safe band
nano.dose,view,condition,denyOps,"doseRatio > 1.0",expression,Block non-emergency nanoswarm ops

nano.psych-env,view,scalar,psychRiskScore,,float,range0,1,Imported R from sleep.subject
nano.psych-env,view,scalar,stimulusBudget,,float,range0,1,Nocturnal stimulus budget
nano.psych-env,view,formula,stimulusBudget,"max(0.0, 1.0 - clamp(psychRiskScore,0,1))",string,readonly,Budget = 1 - R
nano.psych-env,view,condition,requireSoften,"psychRiskScore > 0.5",expression,Require low-intensity scenes/haptics
```

- Mathematical solution: doseRatio is $D_r = D_{\text{day}}/D_{\text{max}}$; any engine summing per-cycle doses into Dday and dividing by the same Dmax will get identical $D_r$; stimulusBudget uses $1 - R$ clamped to $[0,1]$, identical to your compute_nocturnal_stimulus_budget rule.[^3_1]
- Scientific grounding: Conservative dose ceilings and risk-adaptive stimulus budgets match nanomedicine, radiobiology, and neurostimulation practice, where cumulative exposure and current risk constrain intensity and duration.[^3_1]
- Legal terms: Cyberswarm operations SHALL respect daily dose and SAR limits at all times; any doseRatio > 1.0 SHALL trigger automatic suspension of non-emergency functions and a SafetyEpoch ledger entry, and regulators reviewing Phoenix, Santiago, Geneva, or Brussels deployments SHALL be given access to anonymized, hash-linked doseRatio and psychrisk trajectories for oversight.[^3_1]
- Geographical evidence: Boston, USA (nanomedicine and tissue repair), New York, USA (radiation and oncology dosing protocols), Geneva, Switzerland (environmental treaties intersecting with nanotech), Los Alamos/Sandia, USA (materials and exposure models), Phoenix, Arizona, USA (Cyberswarm testbed).[^3_1]

