```

- Mathematical solution: Provenance verification depends on recomputing $h = \text{SHA1}(\text{artifact})$ and checking equality with d2897795d7883360b01f054ba42e0d05f1135d31; SHA-1 is deterministic for given bytes, so any correct implementation with the same artifact must agree on h.[^3_1]
- Scientific grounding: Sigstore DSSE bundles and pinned Fulcio roots give a cryptographically verifiable chain from Reality.os source to Phoenix lab binary, supporting lab and regulator assurance that the same safety logic runs everywhere.[^3_1]
- Legal terms: Neurorights policies in this shard SHALL be non-waivable, SHALL be enforced before any dream-gaming session initializes, and SHALL be coupled to Sigstore-verified artifacts so that regulators or ethics boards in Santiago, Geneva, and Brussels can trace from legal principle to specific, verified code and configuration running on each node.[^3_2][^3_3]
- Geographical evidence: Santiago, Chile (neurorights law proposals), Geneva, Switzerland (human-rights and neurotech fora), Brussels, Belgium (AI Act + Cyber Resilience), San Francisco/Seattle, USA (GitHub/Sigstore infrastructure), Phoenix, Arizona, USA (air-gapped XR rigs where offline verification runs).[^3_2][^3_1]

