- Mathematical solution: $E_x = C(1-r)$ with C=infraComplianceScore and r=riskMetric; any engine using the same scalar inputs and threshold 0.99 will agree on allowExport vs denyExport decisions.[^3_1]
- Scientific grounding: Limiting AI tunnels to anonymized, state-level metrics aligns with best practices where cross-vendor research uses aggregate states but keeps inner content local.[^3_1]
- Legal terms: State-only AI tunnels to Mistral and Qwen SHALL never transmit raw dream narratives, inner speech, or soul-related tags, SHALL be governed by neurorights and brain-data laws in Santiago, Geneva, and Brussels, and SHALL expose logs showing that only whitelisted fields were exported under strict Ex thresholds.[^3_2]
- Geographical evidence: Silicon Valley and Shenzhen (platform and device vendors affected), Geneva (UN neurotech governance), Brussels (AI/data protection), Vancouver and Phoenix (XR/AI research labs using these tunnels).[^3_1]

