Deep-Sleep Token (S)
Binary flag ({0, 1}) indicating stable deep sleep (N2/N3) .
Synaptic downscaling occurs during NREM sleep 42.
Session MUST terminate immediately if S falls to 0 .
Psychriskscore (R)
Continuous scalar [0, 1] reflecting current psychological stress/arousal level .
Not explicitly detailed in provided sources.
Session MUST terminate if R exceeds configured bounds .
Enstasisscore (Es)
Continuous scalar [0, 1] reflecting neural stability/stasis .
Maintains clinically validated stasis levels to prevent destabilization .
Session MUST terminate if Es drops below validated levels .
Threshold (θ)
Minimum eligibility score (e.g., 0.5) required to activate XR-deep .
Pre-configured safety parameter to control access .
Must be pre-registered and adhered to strictly .
This combination of mathematical determinism, grounded in polysomnographic science and fortified by a robust legal framework supported by international and national precedents, creates a highly defensible and reproducible eligibility system. The next step is to validate the analogous safety layers—the Cyberswarm dose limits and psychrisk envelopes—to build a complete picture of the system's technical soundness before attempting to map it to diverse regulatory jurisdictions.

Cyberswarm Dose Limits: Reproducible Radiological Constraints and Medical-Grade Safeguards
The Cyberswarm safety layer represents a critical physical safety boundary within the Reality.os architecture, designed to prevent harmful overexposure to energy fields used for tissue stimulation or repair. Like the eligibility function, its core logic is built upon a foundation of mathematical simplicity and determinism, ensuring that its constraints can be consistently enforced across all deployed platforms. The primary safety calculation is the daily dose ratio, defined by the formula
